MyBarter User Flow - v1: From Discovery to Settlement

  Phase 1: The Storefront (Curation)

Onboarding: User A connects their wallet (Avalanche/Polygon/ETH).

Profile Creation: User A is prompted to link their X Handle and/or Email (Requirement for notifications).

Inventory Scan: The app indexes User A's NFTs and displays them in the "My Collection" tab.

Tagging: User A toggles the "Up for Trade" switch on specific NFTs. These now appear in the public Global Feed.

Presence: User A stays on the site; a "Green Dot" appears on their profile for all other users.

  Phase 2: The Intent (Making the Offer)

Browsing: User B (also with a Green Dot) filters the Global Feed for "LilCoq NFTs" on "Avalanche."

Selection: User B sees an NFT they want and clicks "Make an Offer."

The Bundle: User B selects an NFT from their own collection and adds a $50 Cash Kicker (USDC).

The Lock (The Robot Lawyer): User B clicks "Confirm." They pay the $2.00 Platform Fee and sign a transaction to lock their NFT + USDC into the MyBarter Vault contract.

  Phase 3: The Notification (Closing the Loop)

Immediate Ping: User A receives an in-app notification.

Social Nudge: The MyBarter Bot detects the on-chain lock and automatically posts on X: "Hey @UserA, you've got a live offer on MyBarter from @UserB! Presence: ONLINE 🟢. Check it here: [Link]"

Email Backup: A private email is sent to User A with the trade details.

  Phase 4: The Handshake (Settlement)

Review: User A logs in, sees the offer, and likes the "Cash Kicker" amount.

Acceptance: User A clicks "Accept Trade." They pay their $2.00 Platform Fee and sign the transaction to release their NFT into the vault.

Atomic Swap: The Smart Contract executes the swap simultaneously. User A receives User B's bundle; User B receives User A's NFT.

Completion: The trade is marked "Success" on the Global Activity Ticker.
